{"lemma":"تَلَفُ","slug":"تَلَفُ","root":"ت.ل.ف","root_slug":"ت-ل-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ل-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n4040","n4042","n4043"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perish, to become marred, to be spoiled, to suffer annihilation","examples":[{"text":"وقد تخرج للدابة من حنكها ويسمي التحنيك وصفة العمل في ذلك إذا أحنكت الدابة فأفتح لها من الدرجة الثالثة والرابعة ولا تفتح لها قرب الباب لأن الدم ربما عسر إمساكه فتلف الدابة.","english":"One may extract the blood from the jaw of a beast and it is called taḥnīk and the operation consists in that you have bound the beast with a chinstrap and now cut it open to the third or fourth degree but don’t open it close the throat as it may be difficult to contain the blood and the beast will succumb."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make perish, to spoil, to ruin, to destroy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"destruction","examples":[{"text":"أَصابَ الزَّرْعَ التَّلَفُ."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4040","headword_ar":"تَلِفَ","root":"tlf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talafN","text_ar":"تَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, S, M, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, Lth, T, S, Msb, of any kind, Lth, T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perished, passed away, was not, was no more, became nonexistent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annihilated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away, no one knew whither;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became in a bad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt, state; became corrupted, vitiated, marred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoiled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in this sense the verb is often used in the present"},{"kind":"page_break","n":313},{"kind":"text","text":"day;] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halaka","text_ar":"هَلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and of the inf. n.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaTabN","text_ar":"عَطَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halaAkN","text_ar":"هَلَاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, T, S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talafN","text_ar":"تَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","Lth","T"]},{"entry_id":"n4042","headword_ar":"تَلَفٌ","root":"tlf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A perishing, passing away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. [See 1.] (Lth, T, S, &c.) It is said in a trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a mina","text_ar":"اـِنَّ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqarafi Alt~alafu","text_ar":"القَرَفِ التَّلَفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily, from the being near to pestilence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"epidemic disease, there results death,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perdition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alafu","text_ar":"السَّلَفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talafN","text_ar":"تَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paying for a thing beforehand is a"},{"kind":"text","text":"cause of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perishing"},{"kind":"text","text":"to one's property]. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahabato nafosuhu talafFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَتْ نَفْسُهُ تَلَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalafFA","text_ar":"طَلَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) both meaning the same, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His blood went for nothing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a thing of no account, unretaliated, and uncompensated by a mulct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","T","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n4043","headword_ar":"تَلِفٌ","root":"tlf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAlifN","text_ar":"تَالِفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) part. n. of 1,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (M, Msb, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talofaAnN","text_ar":"تَلْفَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is post-classical. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","TA"]}]}}